    "department": "Builders",
    "description": "Notable is the leading healthcare AI platform for transforming workforce productivity. Health systems, hospitals, and payers use Notable to improve healthcare quality, close gaps in patient care, drive member enrollment, and patient acquisition, retention, and reimbursement, scaling growth without hiring more staff.\n\nWe are on a mission to improve the lives of patients, staff, and clinicians - to improve healthcare for humanity. This isn't just a lofty goal - it's something we're achieving every single day. When you join Notable, you become part of a force actively transforming healthcare. Our aim to impact 100 million patients isn't just a number; it's a commitment to creating meaningful change on a massive scale.\n\nTherefore, our culture is purposeful in pursuit of this mission. We believe our culture gives each person the opportunity to do the best work of their lives, work with the best teammates, and have fun achieving great things together.\n\nRole Summary:\n\nNotable’s Builder Ecosystem is a core strategic initiative. We help healthcare organizations become AI architects, building their own workflows instead of just buying software. This ecosystem includes a Skills marketplace, professional development pathways, and network effects to grow the next generation of health system AI Builders.\n\nWe’re looking for a Program Manager to help design, scale, and optimize this ecosystem. You’ll shape the end-to-end Builder journey, accelerate Builders from trained to production, and ensure the program has what it needs to succeed. You’ll work closely with the Head of Builder Ecosystem on strategy, surface tradeoffs, and translate market intelligence into priorities. You’ll also be the single source of truth for Builder pipeline health, training velocity, and team execution.\n\nThis is a cross-functional role: you’ll connect the Builder Success Lead, Product Marketing Manager, and Head of Builder Ecosystem, providing data, infrastructure, and operational alignment. If you’ve built partner programs, developer ecosystems, or customer enablement operations at a SaaS or platform company and enjoy connecting the dots and driving outcomes, this role will feel familiar.\n\nWhat You’ll Do:\n\n - Program Strategy \u0026 Execution\n   \n   - Partner with the Head of Builder Ecosystem to manage program strategy, roadmap, resources, and tradeoffs.\n   \n   - Track what’s working, flag issues, and recommend solutions.\n   \n   - Design and iterate the end-to-end Builder journey, from awareness to certification to production.\n   \n   - Drive Builder acceleration cohorts and remove strategic blockers.\n\n - Cross-Functional Execution\n   \n   - Keep the team aligned and accountable.\n   \n   - Manage work boards, prioritize initiatives, flag risks, and maintain stakeholder communication across Customer Success, Delivery, and other teams.\n   \n   - Maintain program documentation, knowledge systems, and decision logs.\n\n - Builder Funnel \u0026 Data Operations\n   \n   - Own the Builder CRM as the single source of truth.\n   \n   - Track and analyze the Builder funnel, build predictive models, and identify high potential and at risk Builders.\n   \n   - Deliver data-driven insights that shape strategy, field engagement, and product decisions.\n   \n   - Maintain Builder segmentation and personas to inform nudges and investments.\n\n - Training \u0026 Certification Operations\n   \n   - Manage the training platform, enrollment, pipeline health, and curriculum strategy.\n   \n   - Oversee curriculum contractors, certification processes, and onboarding journeys from day one to first production flow.\n\nYou’re a Great Fit if:\n\n - 5+ years in program management, operations, or enablement roles, running complex cross-functional programs.\n\n - Strong data and analytics skills, comfortable managing CRMs and dashboards.\n\n - Experience in growth-stage companies building infrastructure while running programs.\n\n - Familiarity with AI tools, Asana, Google Workspace, Slack, LMS platforms, BI/analytics tools, and Salesforce.\n\n - Excellent written communication, bias toward action, and ability to drive alignment across teams.\n\n - Ability to travel up to 10% to customer sites\n\nNice to have:\n\n - Healthcare experience, SaaS/platform ecosystem programs, managing training or certification operations, and experience directing contractors or vendors.\n\nHow We Expect You to Work:\n\n - AI-first: leverage AI to scale impact and automate workflows.\n\n - Product-fluent: deeply understand Notable’s platform to identify friction and gaps.\n\n - Builder-minded: You love the 0-\u003e1 phase, create processes, wear multiple hats, and run infrastructure while building it.\n\nWe value in-person collaboration and connection. For Bay Area–based employees, this role requires being in our San Mateo office at least three days a week. For remote employees, occasional travel to headquarters is expected for company-wide events and onsite gatherings.\n\nBeware of job scam fraudsters! Our recruiters use @notablehealth.com email addresses exclusively. We do not conduct interviews via text or instant message, to purchase equipment through us, or to provide sensitive personally identifiable information such as bank account or social security numbers. If you have been contacted by someone claiming to be a recruiter from Notable from a different domain about a job offer, please report it as potential job fraud to law enforcement and contact us here https://www.notablehealth.com/contact.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
